%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20can%20you%20file%20taxes%20in%202026%3F%20Federal%20and%20state%20deadlines%2C%20extensions%2C%20and%20refunds%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228197%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22couple%20doing%20their%20taxes%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F695fc40764858d02d217f9eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225301%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20US%20federal%20tax%20deadline%20is%20April%2015.%3Cp%3EDelmaine%20Donson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20federal%20tax%20filing%20deadline%20for%20most%20Americans%20is%20April%2015%2C%202026.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EState%20tax%20deadlines%20may%20differ%2C%20so%20check%20your%20local%20government%20website%20for%20updates%20and%20extensions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMissing%20forms%20or%20deadlines%20can%20result%20in%20penalties.%20Check%20your%20income%20paperwork%20early.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20that%20time%20of%20year%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftax-saving-strategies-loss-harvesting-stocks-crypto-before-year-end-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETax%20season%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20about%20to%20begin%2C%20and%20most%20Americans%20need%20to%20complete%20their%202025%20filings%20by%20Wednesday%2C%20April%2015.%20To%20avoid%20missing%20a%20deadline%20or%20paying%20a%20penalty%2C%20plan%20to%20check%20your%20local%20tax%20dates%20and%20income%20paperwork%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20everything%20you%20need%20to%20know%20about%20taxes%20in%20the%20new%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224110350b-9ef7-4958-a7e1-ec519e40563f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20can%20I%20file%20taxes%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20submit%20your%202025%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftaxes%2Fwhat-is-a-tax-return%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efederal%20tax%20return%3C%2Fa%3E%20starting%20in%20late%20January%202026.%20Though%20the%20majority%20of%20Americans%20file%20their%20taxes%20annually%2C%20self-employed%20people%2C%20contract%20workers%2C%20and%20some%20gig%20workers%20may%20also%20be%20subject%20to%20quarterly%20estimated%20payment%20deadlines.%20Important%20dates%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EJanuary%2015%2C%202026%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDeadline%20for%20estimated%20tax%20payments%20for%20Q4%202026%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EApril%2015%2C%202026%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20deadline%20for%20individual%20federal%20income%20tax%20returns%20and%20payments%2C%20and%20estimated%20tax%20payments%20for%20Q1%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EJune%2015%2C%202026%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDeadline%20for%20estimated%20tax%20payments%20for%20Q2%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeptember%2015%2C%202026%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDeadline%20for%20estimated%20tax%20payments%20for%20Q3%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EOctober%2015%2C%202026%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EExtended%20deadline%20for%20individual%20income%20tax%20returns%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EJanuary%2015%2C%202027%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDeadline%20for%20estimated%20tax%20payments%20for%20Q4%202026%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETaxes%20for%20Partnerships%20and%20S%20Corporations%20(like%20small%20businesses%20or%20startups)%20are%20due%20on%20March%2015%2C%20and%20taxes%20for%20C%20Corporations%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-digital-tax-cost-us-tech-giants-billions-each-year-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elarger%20companies%20like%20Apple%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Walmart)%20are%20due%20on%20April%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Internal%20Revenue%20Service%20makes%20deadline%20exceptions%20for%20people%20impacted%20by%20federally-recognized%20disasters.%20You%20can%20check%20the%20details%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irs.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Ftax-relief-in-disaster-situations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22096a593b-57f9-472c-aca4-6f402adb99a2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20state%20and%20federal%20deadlines%20different%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20state%20deadlines%20are%20on%20or%20after%20the%20April%2015%20federal%20due%20date%2C%20but%20they%20do%20vary.%20States%20like%20Alabama%2C%20Florida%2C%20Tennessee%2C%20and%20North%20Carolina%20typically%20give%20residents%20a%20longer%20time%20to%20file%20their%20state-level%20taxes%20%E2%80%94%20though%20federal%20filings%20may%20still%20be%20due%20in%20April.%20Check%20your%20state%20government%20website%20for%20updates%20and%20deadline%20extensions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221297b276-4996-4a61-a953-9637a1ef641e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20documents%20do%20I%20need%20to%20file%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-collar-employees-want-loyalty-more-than-money-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esalaried%20employee%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20will%20need%20a%20W-2%20form%20from%20your%20employer%20to%20file%20taxes.%20Contractors%20and%20gig%20workers%20will%20need%20a%201099%20form%20from%20the%20company%20they%20contracted%20with%2C%20and%20self-employed%20workers%20may%20also%20receive%20a%201099%20from%20their%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20paperwork%20is%20typically%20mailed%20to%20Americans%20in%20February%20or%20posted%20online%20through%20their%20payroll%20company.%20Banks%20are%20also%20required%20to%20send%201099s%20to%20people%20who%20received%20interest%20or%20dividends%2C%20and%20those%20who%20sold%20stock%2C%20bonds%2C%20or%20mutual%20funds%20in%202025.%20Some%20inherited%20assets%2C%20like%20real%20estate%2C%20may%20also%20need%20to%20be%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETax%20returns%20will%20likely%20ask%20for%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftaxes%2Fwhat-is-adjusted-gross-income-agi-taxes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadjusted%20gross%20income%20(AGI)%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20your%20total%20earnings%20minus%20certain%20deductions%20like%20student%20loan%20interest%2C%20alimony%20payments%2C%20retirement%20contributions%2C%20and%20health%20savings.%20AGI%20helps%20determine%20your%20eligibility%20for%20tax%20credits%20and%20can%20be%20found%20on%20your%20most%20recent%20tax%20return%20or%20through%20your%20IRS%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20made%20charitable%20contributions%20in%202025%2C%20that%20should%20also%20be%20reported%20in%20your%20filing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ee5cf175-daf8-405e-837f-4792181c8850%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20I%20file%20taxes%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnline%20filing%20is%20the%20most%20efficient%20and%20secure%20way%20to%20organize%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20with%20an%20adjusted%20gross%20income%20at%20or%20below%20%2484%2C000%20may%20qualify%20for%20free%20tax%20preparation%20through%20an%20IRS%20partner.%20Those%20with%20a%20higher%20income%20can%20work%20with%20a%20tax%20advisor%20or%20pay%20for%20online%20tax%20software.%20Pricing%20varies%20depending%20on%20the%20complexity%20of%20individual%20financial%20situations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDirectFile%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-house-republican-kill-irs-direct-file-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efree%20government-run%20tax%20preparation%20service%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20discontinued%20by%20the%20Trump%20administration%20and%20will%20not%20be%20available%20in%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224061159a-436a-49b2-8ad3-1e59e9a50267%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20can%20I%20expect%20a%20refund%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20fully%20filing%20your%20state%20and%20federal%20taxes%2C%20you'll%20see%20if%20you%20owe%20more%20money%20or%20if%20you%20overpaid%20and%20are%20owed%20a%20refund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederal%20and%20state%20refunds%20are%20typically%20sent%20via%20direct%20deposit%20within%20a%20few%20weeks%20of%20filing.%20To%20check%20when%20your%20refund%20is%20coming%2C%20use%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irs.gov%2Frefunds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etracking%20tool%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20IRS%20website.%20You%20will%20need%20to%20provide%20your%20Social%20Security%20number%20or%20taxpayer%20ID%2C%20filing%20status%2C%20and%20exact%20refund%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERefund%20deposits%20could%20take%20longer%20than%20a%20month%20if%20your%20return%20is%20flagged%20for%20errors%2C%20manual%20processing%2C%20or%20potential%20fraud.%20Contact%20the%20IRS%20if%20you%20suspect%20an%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a97ef9ec-bcd9-4796-8771-43d4fcc660ed%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happens%20if%20I%20miss%20a%20tax%20form%20or%20deadline%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20may%20be%20charged%20a%20penalty%20if%20your%20tax%20filing%20is%20missing%20a%20required%20form.%20Having%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftaxes%2Fpenalty-for-filing-taxes-late%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ean%20incomplete%20return%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20April%2015%20federal%20deadline%2C%20for%20example%2C%20will%20result%20in%20a%205%25%20penalty%20per%20month%20on%20any%20unpaid%20tax.%20That%20penalty%20may%20increase%20after%2060%20days%20and%20refunds%20cannot%20be%20processed%20until%20all%20forms%20are%20submitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20prevent%20a%20penalty%2C%20be%20sure%20you%20have%20all%20necessary%20forms%20from%20your%20employer%20before%20the%20deadline.%20If%20your%20employer%20is%20unable%20to%20provide%20this%20paperwork%20in%20time%2C%20contact%20the%20IRS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20get%20an%20automatic%20extension%20by%20paying%20all%20or%20some%20of%20the%20tax%20you%20owe%20by%20the%20April%20deadline.%20Your%20new%20deadline%20will%20be%20October%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f4305912-56c3-43e9-bd0b-42a574ec5443%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happens%20if%20I%20underpaid%20my%20taxes%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20IRS%20or%20your%20state%20tax%20authority%20sends%20a%20notice%20that%20you%20underpaid%20on%20your%202025%20taxes%2C%20try%20to%20pay%20as%20much%20as%20possible%20to%20minimize%20penalties%20and%20interest.%20You'll%20be%20charged%20an%20underpayment%20penalty%20if%20you%20paid%20less%20than%2090%25%20of%20the%20tax%20on%20your%20current-year%20return%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20can%20happen%20if%20your%20employers'%20paycheck%20withholdings%20don't%20cover%20your%20full%20tax%20liability.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-job-hunt-turn-to-self-employment-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESelf-employed%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20independent%20contractors%20can%20be%20charged%20for%20underpayment%20if%20they%20miss%20or%20underpay%20one%20or%20more%20of%20their%20quarterly%20tax%20estimates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20penalty%20only%20applies%20to%20those%20who%20owe%20%241%2C000%20or%20more%20in%20unpaid%20taxes.%20For%20those%20who%20can't%20pay%20the%20full%20underpayment%20balance%20immediately%2C%20the%20IRS%20offers%20short-%20and%20long-term%20payment%20plans.%20The%20interest%20rate%20will%20be%207%25%20in%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20underpayment%20bill%20can%20be%20stressful%2C%20but%20it%20is%20better%20to%20submit%20your%20tax%20returns%20by%20the%20deadline%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20you%20can't%20afford%20your%20full%20balance.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftaxes%2Fwhat-happens-if-you-dont-file-taxes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIRS'%20failure-to-file%20penalty%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20higher%20than%20the%20underpayment%20penalty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20IRS%20doesn't%20report%20this%20to%20major%20credit%20bureaus%2C%20so%20a%20tax%20underpayment%20will%20not%20directly%20impact%20your%20credit%20score.%20Steep%20tax%20debt%20over%20time%2C%20however%2C%20could%20be%20sent%20to%20a%20collections%