r%2C%20he%20would%20often%20advise%20those%20working%20for%20him%20to%20take%20PTO%2C%20but%20said%20he%20sometimes%20secretly%20resented%20it%20when%20they%20did.%20Attending%20a%2010-day%20silent%20retreat%20changed%20his%20perspective.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20brevity%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20dad%20was%20an%20entrepreneur%2C%20but%20he%20would%20never%20take%20vacation.%20It%20was%20this%20mindset%20of%20always%20being%20on.%20So%2C%20in%20the%20back%20of%20my%20mind%2C%20there%20was%20always%20this%20guilt%20about%20vacation.%20That's%20persisted%20for%20most%20of%20my%20life%2C%20and%20I've%20been%20a%20founder%20a%20couple%20of%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20tell%20people%20to%20take%20time%20off%2C%20but%20my%20tone%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BTake%20only%20a%20week%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Btake%20just%20enough.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20our%20top-performing%20employees%20takes%20long%20vacations%2C%20but%20then%20they're%20unbelievably%20productive.%20I%20would%20always%20be%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BShould%20you%20be%20taking%20that%20time%20off%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20was%20feeling%20resentful%20and%20annoyed%2C%20even%20though%2C%20logically%2C%20I%20shouldn't%20feel%20that%20way.%20They're%20so%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20married%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20my%20wife%20is%20much%20more%20balanced%20with%20these%20things.%20We%20went%20on%20a%20couple%20of%20vacations%2C%20where%20I%20was%20working.%20Last%20year%2C%20we%20took%20a%20vacation%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20work%2C%20but%20I%20wasn't%20mentally%20there.%20I%20had%20anxiety%20about%20work%2C%20about%20getting%20things%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224c307b0f-122d-4d54-bcf9-7163be2e6f77%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EReaching%20'terminal%20burnout'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20see%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20my%20age%20focused%20on%20%3Cem%3Eachieve%2C%20achieve%2C%20achieve%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%20get%20into%20a%20great%20school%2C%20get%20a%20prestigious%20job.%20And%20then%20you're%20in%20your%20mid-30s%2C%20and%20you're%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20am%20I%20working%20toward%3F%26quot%3B%20That%20type%20of%20anxiety%20makes%20you%20always%20look%20for%20endorphins%20and%20achievement%2C%20and%20that's%20what%20I%20was%20tortured%20by%20a%20lot%20on%20vacation%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20I%20probably%20reached%20a%20level%20of%20terminal%20burnout%2C%20where%20you're%20so%20overwhelmed%20and%20stuck%20in%20the%20weeds%20that%20you%20just%20can't%20actually%20disconnect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20struggling%20to%20enjoy%20experiences%20that%20are%20supposed%20to%20be%20fun.%20When%20you're%20working%2C%20it's%20great%2C%20but%20when%20you're%20hanging%20out%20with%20your%20wife%20or%20friends%2C%20you're%20unable%20to%20disconnect.%20You%20keep%20thinking%20about%20work%3B%20you%20keep%20feeling%20anxious%20about%20things%20that%20you%20shouldn't%20feel%20anxious%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20gone%20through%20therapy.%20I%20tried%20meditation%2C%20but%20sometimes%20you%20just%20need%20time%20off.%20I%20don't%20think%20there's%20a%20replacement%20for%20just%20stopping%2C%20because%20otherwise%20you're%20still%20in%20that%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheoretically%2C%20I%20always%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20important%20to%20take%20vacation.%26quot%3B%20I%20understand%20the%20concept%2C%20but%20burnout%20got%20really%20bad%20for%20me%20last%20year.%20I%20was%20also%20dealing%20with%20some%20family%20stuff%2C%20and%2C%20on%20their%20own%2C%20those%20things%20would%20have%20been%20fine%2C%20but%20coupled%20with%20work%2C%20they%20just%20built%20up.%20I%20was%20really%20miserable%20and%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2292ae236c-5449-4885-8e71-e9b68ddfce77%5C%22%3EThe%20retreat%20that%20changed%20my%20mindset%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20tried%20to%20take%20a%20day%20off%20or%20meditate%2C%20it%20wasn't%20working.%20I%20would%20get%20pulled%20into%20distractio