e%20first%20or%20last%20time%20someone%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bwitty%26quot%3B%20one-liner%20about%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstop-spending-money-for-week-family-on-budget-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efamily%20size%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20completely%20on%20purpose%20and%20by%20choice%2C%20if%20they%20must%20know.%20My%20kids%20jumped%20into%20the%20playground%20with%20the%20others%2C%20and%20I%20settled%20in%20to%20find%20my%20new%20besties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221179%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mom%20and%20daughter%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69614b3a832e0ef1ead78114%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22884%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20felt%20her%20parenting%20style%20didn't%20match%20that%20of%20her%20moms'%20group.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thing%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa-mom-shares-how-facebook-parenting-groups-can-be-lifesaving-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emom%20groups%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%2C%20is%20that%20they%20often%20aren't%20obviously%20terrible.%20In%20fact%2C%20they%20check%20all%20the%20boxes%20%E2%80%94%20moms%20at%20similar%20ages%2C%20stages%2C%20and%20struggles%2C%20getting%20together%20for%20camaraderie%20and%20community.%20We%20all%20had%20similar%20jogger%20set%20mom%20uniforms%20and%20extra-strong%20lattes%20on%20hand%2C%20hidden%20in%20the%20pockets%20of%20diaper%20bags%20to%20make%20it%20past%20%26quot%3Bno%20food%20or%20drink%26quot%3B%20signs%20at%20indoor%20parks%20(no%3F%20Just%20me%3F).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20they%20aren't%20always%20necessarily%20a%20good%20fit.%20All%20the%20feelings%20from%20this%20almost-perfect%20mom%20group%20I%20was%20once%20a%20part%20of%20resurfaced%20when%20Ashley%20Tisdale%20wrote%20an%20essay%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thecut.com%2Farticle%2Fashley-tisdale-french-mom-group-mean-girls-parenting.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Cut%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20talking%20openly%20about%20how%20her%20mom%20group%20turned%20toxic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2287b8503e-b760-4897-aa3b-01cfa14a38de%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'm%20a%20free-range%20parent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20feelings%20that%20I%20was%20%26quot%3Bdifferent%26quot%3B%20came%20when%20two%20of%20the%20younger%20kids%20had%20a%20small%20collision%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20a%20slide.%20They%20tripped%2C%20fussed%20a%20bit%2C%20and%20in%20my%20parenting%20world%2C%20were%20ready%20to%20get%20back%20up%20and%20carry%20on.%20I'm%20used%20to%20being%20around%20people%20with%20widely%20differing%20parenting%20styles%2C%20but%20not%20used%20to%20being%20judged%20for%20mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20like%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffree-range-parenting-mom-lets-kids-fly-alone-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efree-range%20parenting%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20judged%20by%20other%20moms%20who%20were%20more%20helicopter%20parents.%20The%20mom%20of%20the%20other%20kid%20who%20collided%20picked%20the%20child%20up%2C%20brushed%20them%20up%2C%20and%20performed%20a%20full%20check-up.%20Meanwhile%2C%20my%20own%20child%20popped%20up%2C%20whined%20a%20little%2C%20and%20ran%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221069%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Boy%20in%20park%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F696179e304eda4732f2ed67d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22802%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20needed%20a%20safe%20space%20to%20vent%20and%20felt%20like%20the%20group%20she%20found%20was%20not%20it.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBand-Aids%20and%20tissues%20were%20coming%20out%20to%20counteract%20tears%2C%20and%20a%20full-scale%20breakdown%20of%20the%20situation%2C%20complete%20with%20apologies%20and%20moment-by-moment%20recaps%2C%20had%20commenced.%20I%20enjoyed%20my%20coffee%20and%20didn't%20give%20it%20much%20thought.%20I%20hadn't%20noticed%20yet%20that%20my%20parenting%20style%20was%20a%20mismatch.%20To%20be%20clear%2C%20this%20is%20just%20my%20perception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22519e122a-ab9e-4f1b-8b68-44ab0d9c3bd1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20needed%20a%20place%20to%20vent%20and%20feel%20safe%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESlowly%20but%20surely%2C%20questions%20about%20my%20family%20size%20began%20to%20infiltrate%20conversations.%20I%20was%20used%20to%20one-liners%20from%20grannies%20at%20the%20grocery%20about%20having%20my%20hands%20full%2C%20but%20it%20felt%20like%20an%20onslaught.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20same%20thing%20with%20my%20career.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAfter%20the%20group%20learned%20I%20was%20a%20working%20mom%2C%20running%20my%20own%20business%20full-time%2C%20I%20started%20to%20feel%20like%20an%20outsider.%20People%20spoke%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20negative%20sides%20of%20daycare%2C%20and%20the%20perks%20of%20being%20able%20to%20be%20a%20full-time%20mom%2C%20Their%20comments%20made%20it%20seem%20they%20weren't%20interested%20in%20a%20different%20perspective%2C%20nor%20was%20there%20a%20question%20about%20why%20I%20work%20(because%20I%20want%20to)%20or%20about%20the%20immense%20benefits%20my%20kids%20have%20gotten%20through%20day%20care.%20I%20felt%20like%20there%20was%20an%20assumption%20that%20I%20was%20stuck%20in%20this%20terrible%20world%20of%20working%20motherhood%20against%20my%20will%2C%20with%20no%20way%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20the%20circus%20spectacle%2C%20and%20felt%20I%20had%20to%20have%20all%20the%20i's%20dotted%20and%20t's%20crossed%20on%20parenting%20topics%2C%20to%20show%20the%20naysayers%20that%20I%20was%20doing%20just%20fine%20with%20many%20kids%2C%20rather%20than%20finding%20a%20soft%20landing%20place%20to%20vent%20and%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2273dc4ae7-e35c-4145-adb3-001075522ec7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EParenting%20can%20be%20so%20isolating%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20lonely%20and%20desperate%2C%20so%20I%20clung%20to%20my%20mom%20group.%20The%20alternative%20was%20too%20scary.%20Nobody%20to%20hang%20out%20with%20on%20a%20boring%20Saturday%20or%20text%20when%20things%20get%20tough.%20It's%20not%20just%20me%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fosuwmc.multimedia-newsroom.com%2Findex.php%2F2024%2F04%2F24%2Fsurvey-finds-loneliness-epidemic-runs-deep-among-parents%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo-thirds%20of%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%20find%20the%20role%20isolating%20and%20lonely.%20But%20one%20day%2C%20I%20realized%20the%20abyss%20was%20better%20than%20the%20alternative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20day%20they%20moved%20all%20the%20get-togethers%20to%2010%20a.m.%20on%20weekdays.%20They%20knew%20exactly%20where%20I'd%20be%20at%2010%20a.m.%20every%20weekday%20%E2%80%94%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20I%20haven't%20found%20a%20similar%20style%20group%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20instead%20of%20looking%20for%20a%20whole%20village%20of%20besties%2C%20my%20village%20was%20already%20around%20me.%20It%20just%20didn't%20look%20like%2010%20moms%20with%20lattes%20at%20play%20group.%20Instead%2C%20it%20involves%20the%20trainer%20who%20asks%20if%20my%20kid%20is%20over%20his%20third%20bout%20of%20strep%2C%20or%20my%20mom's%20friend%20who%20texts%20me%20with%20some%20press-on%20nails%20she%20likes%20that%20would%20look%20good%20on%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20real%20friends%20don't%20demand%20we%20have%20precisely%20only%201.5%20children%2C%20helicopter%20around%20our%20babies%2C%20or%20only%20wear%20pink%20on%20Wednesdays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftoxic-mom-group-judgment-why-i-left-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767995925000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22htt